11. &ldquo;I am a Hindu communalist&rdquo;
 A symptom of the ideological power equation is the Sangh  Parivar&rsquo;s permanent checkmate in the &ldquo;war of the words&rdquo;. The Sangh is at the mercy of the meanings which its enemies allot to important terms, such as &ldquo;communalism&rdquo;.
 Originally (at least in Indian politics), &quot;communal&quot; was the  term by which the British labelled political arrangements, such as separate electorates and quota-based recruitment, which took the religious community as the operative unit rather than the individual or the family or the region or the nation.

